  "target_response": {
    "text": "Reasonable — 3 kg by September is nowhere near crash-diet territory. From 78.6 kg to your 75.6 kg target across roughly nine weeks works out to about 0.3 kg a week, well inside the commonly used ceiling of 1% of bodyweight per week. At that pace you can eat a modest deficit, keep protein up, and train normally, which is what protects strength and energy on the trail. Frame it as a progress target rather than a daily verdict: weigh a few times a week, judge only the weekly average, and expect flat stretches — water swings hide fat change for days at a time. First milestone: if the weekly average is down about a kilo after three weeks, hold the plan; if it hasn't moved, trim intake slightly rather than adding punishment cardio.",
